Package specific

Class Individual

  • java.lang.Object
    • specific.Individual
  • public class Individual
extends java.lang.Object
    The Individual is associated with a path of points in a map, and therefore with a correspondent cost and comfort. It's also associated to a Population of individuals and to it's lifetime events (Death,Move and Reproduction).

    This class provides methods to add points to the path of the Individual, recalculating it's comfort and cost. Note that the methods are implemented in such a way that when there is a point added to the path that is already on it, the corresponding cycle is eliminated.

    See Also:
    Map, Population, Death, Move, Reproduction

    • Method Detail

      • getPathIndividual

        protected Individual getPathIndividual()
        Creates and returns a copy of this Individual, based only on it's path, comfort and cost.

        The path is a deep copy of the path, in order to assure that isnï¿½t altered by any changes that might occur in the path of this Individual. The rest of the attributes of the individual are set to null.

        Returns:
        an Individual with a copy of the comfort, cost and a deep copy of the path of the current Individual.

      • addToPath

        protected void addToPath​(Point new_point)
        Add a new point to the path and updates the cost and comfort accordingly. This method first checks if the new position introduces a cycle in the path (with the checkCycle method). If there is a cycle, the corresponding points are deleted from the path (method breakCycle). If a cycle isn't detected, it adds the new point (method addNewPoint).
        Parameters:
        new_point - - new position of the map to add to the path

      • addNewPoint

        protected void addNewPoint​(Point new_point)
        Adds a new point to path if there is no cycle with its introduction, and recalculates the new cost.

        This method should be used only after checking if there is a cycle.

        Parameters:
        new_point - - point to add to path

      • checkCycle

        private boolean checkCycle​(Point point)
        Checks if a position already exists in the path (if there is a cycle).
        Parameters:
        point - - point we wish to test.
        Returns:
        true if there will be a cycle in the path with the new point. False if not.

      • breakCycle

        private void breakCycle​(Point newPoint)
        Breaks a cycle in the path by eliminating the corresponding points until the repeated point, and updates cost accordingly.

        This method should be used only if a cycle was detected.

        Parameters:
        newPoint - - repeated point in the path
